    <sect1>
        <title>Camera Setup</title>
        <para>I use my Samsung Galaxy S5 Active mounted in Kickstarter version of the Beastgrip
                (<link xlink:href="https://beastgrip.com/"/>). This allows me to add a zoom
            lens,which I haven't been able to afford yet, but also gives nice mounting holes for a
            tripod.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>Camera</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="Camera.jpg" contentdepth="100%" scalefit="1" width="100%"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        <para>Using a tripod gets the camera angle up high enough to eliminate most of the paralax
            when displaying the projector screen, but it also eliminates the reflexion of the lights
            on the white board.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>Camera</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="Tripod.jpg" contentdepth="100%" scalefit="1" width="100%"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
